The paper deals with approximation algorithms for clustering problems, which are typically studied in the areas of data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), machine learning (cs.LG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and game theory (cs.GT). The use of doubling metrics is also a characteristic of these areas. Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
